==English==
===Etymology===
A corruption of Arabic {{ARchar|[[رجل]]}} (rijl) ‘foot, leg’, in the Arabic name {{ARchar|الرجل الجبار}} (ar-rijl al-jabbār) ‘the foot of the great one’. [[Category:Arabic derivations]]

===Synonyms===
*[[Algebar]] 
*[[Elgebar]]
===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Rigel'''

#{{star}}: A [[supergiant]] [[star]] in the [[constellation]] [[Orion]]; Beta (β) Orionis. The seventh brightest star in the night sky.

